OL,5, The omission from the Queen's Speech of
OL,6, measures to improve workers' rights has
OL,7, been met with backlash.                
OL,9,FFlexible working rights, protections   
OL,10,Fagainst pregnancy discrimination, and  
OL,11,Frights for staff to keep all tips had  
OL,12,Fbeen hoped for in an Employment Bill.  
OL,14,FPlans for the bill were first announced
OL,15,Fby the government in 2019.             
OL,17,FUnions accused the government of       
OL,18,F"turning its back" on workers while    
OL,19,Findustry groups said they were         
OL,20,Fdisappointed the bill had been omitted.
